======================================================================
PART 2: k=1 FINITE DIFFERENCE (ARC-FLIP DELTAS)
  Delta_e H = H(T) - H(T flip e)
  This is our familiar arc-flip spectrum
======================================================================

--- n = 4 ---
  Delta_e H distribution: {-4: 24, -2: 96, 0: 144, 2: 96, 4: 24}
  All deltas even: True
  Symmetric: True

--- n = 5 ---
  Delta_e H distribution: {-12: 40, -8: 360, -6: 600, -4: 1200, -2: 1800, 0: 2240, 2: 1800, 4: 1200, 6: 600, 8: 360, 12: 40}
  All deltas even: True
  Symmetric: True

======================================================================
PART 3: k=2 FINITE DIFFERENCE
  Delta_{e1,e2} H = H(T) - H(T^e1) - H(T^e2) + H(T^{e1,e2})
  If all zero, H would be of type 1 (linear in arc flips)
======================================================================

--- n = 4 ---
  Total tests: 960
  Delta_2 distribution: {-2: 384, 0: 192, 2: 384}
  All zero: False

  Adjacent vs non-adjacent arc pairs:
    Adjacent arcs (shared vertex): {-2: 384, 2: 384}
    Non-adjacent arcs (disjoint): {0: 192}

--- n = 5 ---
  Total tests: 9000
  Delta_2 distribution: {-6: 161, -4: 1218, -2: 2493, 0: 1542, 2: 2321, 4: 1124, 6: 141}
  All zero: False

  Adjacent vs non-adjacent arc pairs:
