    Non-adjacent arcs (disjoint): {-4: 61, -2: 317, 0: 758, 2: 307, 4: 57}

======================================================================
PART 4: DISJOINT ARC PAIRS — IS H ADDITIVE ON DISJOINT FLIPS?
  If Delta_{e1,e2} H = 0 for disjoint arcs, then H decomposes
  as a sum of 'local' contributions from vertex neighborhoods
======================================================================

--- n = 5 ---
  Total disjoint pair tests: 7500
  Disjoint Delta_2 distribution: {-4: 293, -2: 1652, 0: 3615, 2: 1648, 4: 292}
  All zero (additive on disjoint flips): False

--- n = 6 ---
  Total disjoint pair tests: 10035
  Disjoint Delta_2 distribution: {-16: 20, -12: 32, -10: 88, -8: 203, -6: 396, -4: 1079, -2: 1785, 0: 2901, 2: 1776, 4: 1042, 6: 383, 8: 209, 10: 66, 12: 43, 16: 12}
  All zero (additive on disjoint flips): False

======================================================================
PART 5: 3-CYCLE REVERSAL AS 3-ARC FLIP
  Reversing a 3-cycle = flipping 3 arcs simultaneously
  This is the 'Reidemeister R3' move
  Already verified: H-invariant at n=4, NOT at n>=5
  New question: Delta_3 on 3-cycle arc triples?
======================================================================

--- n = 5 ---
  3-cycle triples: Delta_3 distribution: {0: 426}
  Non-cycle triples: Delta_3 distribution: {0: 1574}
  3-cycle Delta_3 all zero: True

